WEBVTT

00:00.401 --> 00:01.467
ADULT ADAM:
<i> When I was kid,</i>

00:01.469 --> 00:03.235
<i> my mom would use</i>
<i> every opportunity</i>

00:03.237 --> 00:05.904
<i> to squeeze, smooch,</i>
<i> and snuggle her schmoopies.</i>

00:05.906 --> 00:08.007
<i> There was only one time</i>
<i> she expected us</i>

00:08.009 --> 00:10.342
<i> to do it in return...</i>
<i> Mother's Day.</i>

00:10.344 --> 00:12.277
<i> Naturally, we'd use</i>
<i> the opportunity</i>

00:12.279 --> 00:14.146
<i> to mess with her</i>
<i> for a cheap laugh.</i>

00:14.148 --> 00:15.647
Oh, look at my
special calendar

00:15.649 --> 00:17.116
hanging in a
high-traffic area.

00:17.118 --> 00:18.050
How'd that get there?

00:18.052 --> 00:19.485
That's odd.
Didn't notice.

00:19.487 --> 00:21.086
You wanna take a peek,

00:21.088 --> 00:23.389
see if there's
any special day in May

00:23.391 --> 00:24.323
that you need to remember?

00:24.325 --> 00:25.524
Nah, I got Cinco de Mayo
on lock.

00:25.526 --> 00:27.826
I think she's talking
about French Labor Day.

00:27.828 --> 00:29.294
No, it's
<i> Star Wars</i> Day!

00:29.296 --> 00:31.497
May the 4th be
with you, right?

00:31.499 --> 00:32.798
How could I forget!
That's right!

00:32.800 --> 00:34.767
I gotta go shopping.
I love<i> Star Wars</i> Day.

00:34.769 --> 00:36.068
So do I!
No, no.

00:36.070 --> 00:37.169
How did I forget?
Can I give you a hint?

00:37.171 --> 00:38.704
ADULT ADAM:<i> Yep, nothing</i>
<i> brought us kids closer</i>

00:38.706 --> 00:41.440
<i> than using Mother's Day</i>
<i> to torture Beverly Goldberg.</i>

00:41.442 --> 00:44.610
(GASPS) What?
You're home from
school already?

00:44.612 --> 00:45.044
What a surprise.

00:45.046 --> 00:47.813
I was just going through these
beautiful handwritten cards

00:47.815 --> 00:49.281
you gave me
almost a year ago exactly.

00:49.283 --> 00:52.484
Maybe you should come and take
a closer look at this cards,

00:52.486 --> 00:54.286
get a sense
of what they're about

00:54.288 --> 00:55.421
and how they make me feel?

00:55.423 --> 00:56.889
Enough jibber-jabber.

00:56.891 --> 00:58.357
I need a pre-dinner meal...

00:58.359 --> 01:00.726
Maybe something
that'll lay a nice base,

01:00.728 --> 01:01.960
like pancakes.

01:01.962 --> 01:02.694
Screw it. I give up.

01:02.696 --> 01:04.930
Murray, you are taking me
to that Latin place

01:04.932 --> 01:07.166
on Saturday night,
and we are gonna cha-cha

01:07.168 --> 01:08.467
'cause these kids
are ungrateful.

01:08.469 --> 01:10.402
No, I am not
going to cha-cha.

01:10.404 --> 01:13.639
Oh, you will cha-cha,
and I will be dipped.

01:13.641 --> 01:16.475
And you won't drop me
this time.

01:16.477 --> 01:18.677
All right, you've had
enough fun, you morons.

01:18.679 --> 01:20.846
Go tell your mom that
you know it's Mother's Day.

01:20.848 --> 01:23.282
Aw, but we look forward to
torturing her all year long.

01:23.284 --> 01:25.818
It's one of our
better family traditions.

01:25.820 --> 01:26.685
Do it!

01:26.687 --> 01:28.387
(SIGHS) Hey, Mom?

01:28.389 --> 01:32.157
We just realized
that Mother's Day
is this weekend.

01:32.159 --> 01:34.493
What? I had no idea.

01:34.495 --> 01:36.628
Oh, I can't believe
you remembered.

01:36.630 --> 01:39.264
Oh, I just love
my children so much.

01:39.266 --> 01:41.233
Here comes a tearful hug.

01:41.235 --> 01:42.768
Sacrifice the nerd
and run!

01:42.770 --> 01:45.437
(LAUGHING)
Oh, my favorite!

01:45.439 --> 01:47.106
Tell my story!

01:47.108 --> 01:48.474
<i> ¶ I'm twisted up inside</i>

01:48.476 --> 01:52.678
<i> ¶ But nonetheless</i>
<i> I feel the need to say</i>

01:54.648 --> 01:55.814
<i> ¶ I don't know the future</i>

01:55.816 --> 02:00.285
<i> ¶ But the past keeps getting</i>
<i> clearer every day ¶</i>

02:00.287 --> 02:02.187
ADULT ADAM:
<i> It was May 3,</i>
<i> 1980-something,</i>

02:02.189 --> 02:04.289
<i> and my brother and his pals</i>
<i> were about to watch</i>

02:04.291 --> 02:06.625
<i> the most famous TV movie</i>
<i> of the decade.</i>

02:06.627 --> 02:08.627
Dad, I demand
you give me the remote

02:08.629 --> 02:11.563
and go make us nachos
as we watch your TV
without you.

02:11.565 --> 02:13.465
Did you really think
that would work?
No.

02:13.467 --> 02:15.134
Yes! Now we're gonna miss
the whole movie.

02:15.136 --> 02:17.669
I got a Sony Watchman.
All we need is
nine batteries.

02:17.671 --> 02:18.770
All we need
is nine batteries.

02:18.772 --> 02:19.972
What are you dummies
going on about?

02:19.974 --> 02:22.941
Tonight, they're airing
a gnarly made-for-TV movie

02:22.943 --> 02:23.675
called<i> The Day After,</i>

02:23.677 --> 02:26.145
where America's in a
nuclear war with Russia.

02:26.147 --> 02:27.279
Ka-boom!
America!

02:27.281 --> 02:27.813
Jason Robards, y'all!

02:27.815 --> 02:30.782
All of the teachers at school
warned us not to see it,

02:30.784 --> 02:31.717
so we have to watch it

02:31.719 --> 02:33.218
to send a clear message
of "Suck it."

02:33.220 --> 02:35.254
If I say yes,
will you shut up?

02:35.256 --> 02:35.721
This is gonna rock!

02:35.723 --> 02:38.724
ADULT ADAM:
<i> But it did not rock.</i>
<i> Not at all.</i>

02:38.726 --> 02:41.727
This does not rock.
Not at all!

02:41.729 --> 02:42.895
ADULT ADAM:
<i> Turns out,</i> The Day After

02:42.897 --> 02:45.264
<i> was a terrifying</i>
<i> and all-too-real depiction</i>

02:45.266 --> 02:47.666
<i> of a small town just like ours</i>
<i> facing the fallout</i>

02:47.668 --> 02:51.336
<i> after the President waged</i>
<i> a horrible nuclear war.</i>

02:51.338 --> 02:52.938
Too real.
War is bad.

02:52.940 --> 02:54.840
So scared.
I'll never be okay.

02:54.842 --> 02:56.441
I like that Steve Guttenberg.

02:56.443 --> 02:57.176
He's got a lot of range.

02:57.178 --> 03:00.012
Dad, don't you care
about what you just saw?

03:00.014 --> 03:01.280
There could be
a mushroom cloud

03:01.282 --> 03:02.281
outside our window
at any moment!

03:02.283 --> 03:05.217
I say, "Bring on the cloud,"
'cause then maybe
you'll shut up

03:05.219 --> 03:06.485
and I can get back
to watching my shows.

03:06.487 --> 03:10.422
ADULT ADAM:
<i> That night, the entire country</i>
<i> watched that movie,</i>

03:10.424 --> 03:11.423
<i> and legit panic ensued.</i>

03:11.425 --> 03:13.559
Okay, students,
even though we
warned you all

03:13.561 --> 03:15.394
not to watch that
terrifying TV movie,

03:15.396 --> 03:17.863
apparently everyone
in this school did,

03:17.865 --> 03:19.398
as well as
100 million other people.

03:19.400 --> 03:22.768
Therefore, we are going to
have an emergency meeting

03:22.770 --> 03:25.504
entitled "The Day After
<i> 'The Day After.'"</i>

03:25.506 --> 03:26.205
Of course,
the gym is booked,

03:26.207 --> 03:29.942
so it'll be "The Day After
The Day After
<i> 'The Day After.'"</i>

03:29.944 --> 03:30.876
So, Wednesday.

03:30.878 --> 03:32.311
Oh, my God.
How are you?

03:32.313 --> 03:33.679
I had nightmares
all night.

03:33.681 --> 03:34.513
I didn't watch
the movie.

03:34.515 --> 03:37.015
I spent the night
organizing my
Garbage Pail Kids

03:37.017 --> 03:37.883
into a protective binder.

03:37.885 --> 03:40.485
Don't want you to feel
like things are going
too fast,

03:40.487 --> 03:41.954
but this is our nest egg.

03:41.956 --> 03:43.388
Well, after watching
that movie,

03:43.390 --> 03:45.991
I realized we don't have
any time to waste.

03:45.993 --> 03:47.726
We should have
our first kiss,

03:47.728 --> 03:48.827
right here, right now.

03:48.829 --> 03:50.796
We talking cheek or lips?

03:55.536 --> 03:56.802
Uh...

03:57.404 --> 03:58.804
Thank you.

03:59.340 --> 04:00.939
I'm a big fan,
big fan of you.

04:00.941 --> 04:03.275
Listen, my parents
are renting a house

04:03.277 --> 04:04.643
at the shore this weekend.

04:04.645 --> 04:05.210
Come with me.

04:05.212 --> 04:06.878
We'll spend each moment
like it's our last.

04:06.880 --> 04:08.380
What is the deal
with this movie?

04:08.382 --> 04:10.349
My mom said
I could bring someone,

04:10.351 --> 04:12.651
Well, okay, then!
so I choose you.

04:15.289 --> 04:18.423
<i> The Day After</i> is
the best movie ever!
(CHUCKLES)

04:18.425 --> 04:22.694
Oh, my God, she just
invited you down the shore!

04:22.696 --> 04:23.161
I know, Dave Kim.

04:23.163 --> 04:25.364
But your mom
will never say yes.
I know, Dave Kim!

04:25.366 --> 04:27.432
You gotta
think of something.
I know, Dave Kim.

04:27.434 --> 04:28.834
ADULT ADAM:<i> Lucky for me,</i>
<i> the timing was perfect.</i>

04:28.836 --> 04:31.270
(BETTE MIDLER'S
<i> WIND BENEATH MY WINGS</i> PLAYS)
<i> It was Mother's Day.</i>

04:31.272 --> 04:33.438
<i> I'd strike hard and fast</i>
<i> with a schmaltzy gift</i>

04:33.440 --> 04:36.074
<i> featuring the vocal power</i>
<i> of Bette Midler.</i>

04:36.076 --> 04:38.443
<i> It would make my mom</i>
<i> say yes to anything.</i>

04:38.445 --> 04:43.181
<i> ¶ I can fly higher</i>
<i> than an eagle</i>

04:45.953 --> 04:52.057
<i> ¶ 'Cause you are the wind</i>
<i> beneath my wings ¶</i>

04:53.160 --> 04:56.795
ADULT ADAM:
<i> Unfortunately, my sister</i>
<i> had the exact same plan.</i>

04:56.797 --> 04:59.264
This is pandering garbage!
You can't do this.

04:59.266 --> 04:59.665
Why not?

04:59.667 --> 05:02.000
Because I'm working
on my own pandering garbage

05:02.002 --> 05:05.370
so that Mom will
let me go to college
5,000 miles away.

05:05.372 --> 05:06.238
Emory is in Georgia.

05:06.240 --> 05:08.106
That's why I need to ask her
on Mother's Day,

05:08.108 --> 05:09.975
when she's all buttered up
and distracted.

05:09.977 --> 05:11.777
But we can't both
lower Mom's defenses

05:11.779 --> 05:14.246
with an insincere, theatrical
show of our love.

05:14.248 --> 05:16.181
Well, you're just
gonna have to back down.

05:16.183 --> 05:19.384
Your dumb thing is
way less important
than college.

05:19.386 --> 05:20.352
But when will
I have the chance

05:20.354 --> 05:22.521
to rub cocoa butter
on my lady's shoulders again?

05:22.523 --> 05:24.523
Honestly, I can't imagine
you ever will.

05:24.525 --> 05:27.125
But still,
this is my whole future.

05:27.127 --> 05:29.061
Okay, fine.
I'll back down.

05:29.063 --> 05:30.295
But only 'cause
you're my sister

05:30.297 --> 05:33.031
and I love you,
so I'll let you have this one.

05:33.033 --> 05:34.633
And you lose, sucker!

05:34.835 --> 05:36.601
Adam, stop!
You stop!

05:36.603 --> 05:37.803
Stop!

05:38.172 --> 05:39.071
Okay, everyone,

05:39.073 --> 05:42.941
welcome to "The Day After"
emergency assembly.

05:42.943 --> 05:45.410
First of all,
I just want to assure you

05:45.412 --> 05:47.179
that everything
is gonna be okay.

05:47.181 --> 05:48.280
It will not be okay!

05:48.282 --> 05:50.949
There's nowhere to hide
in a nuclear winter!
Whoa. (CHUCKLES)

05:50.951 --> 05:53.819
What Coach means is
that there could be
a nuclear winter,

05:53.821 --> 05:54.753
but it definitely
won't happen.

05:54.755 --> 05:58.557
Till it does.
Does not, because
it was just a movie.

05:58.559 --> 05:59.958
That will, for sure,
come true.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.393
Look, I know
a lot of you are scared

06:01.395 --> 06:04.229
that the President is gonna
snap, push a button,

06:04.231 --> 06:05.197
and incinerate us all,

06:05.199 --> 06:07.432
but I assure you,
it will not happen.

06:07.434 --> 06:10.369
When it does,
I'll be safe and snug

06:10.371 --> 06:11.169
in my fallout shelter

06:11.171 --> 06:15.240
while the rest of you mutants
scrounge for cockroaches.

06:16.043 --> 06:17.909
What, you got no argument
for that one?

06:17.911 --> 06:18.643
No, you're right.

06:18.645 --> 06:20.679
That movie has shaken me
to my core.

06:20.681 --> 06:21.713
I have so many regrets.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.482
You got about a week
to fix 'em, Andre.

06:23.484 --> 06:25.717
Well, let's start
with that one right there.

06:25.719 --> 06:27.452
My name is not Andre.

06:27.454 --> 06:28.720
I only said it was
in college

06:28.722 --> 06:31.556
to make myself seem
more interesting
to the ladies.

06:31.558 --> 06:34.025
Let it out!
My name is Jonathan!

06:34.027 --> 06:36.628
And I love you,
Lunch Lady Bernice!

06:36.630 --> 06:38.563
Are you out there?

06:39.566 --> 06:42.434
MR. GLASCOTT: You're probably
mashing potatoes.

06:43.137 --> 06:43.935
Oh, boy.

06:43.937 --> 06:45.971
Okay,
this day is a wash.

06:45.973 --> 06:48.540
Everybody go home
and hug your loved ones.

06:48.542 --> 06:50.075
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

06:50.077 --> 06:52.043
I know I should be happy
to have the day off,

06:52.045 --> 06:53.612
but I'm, like,
genuinely terrified.

06:53.614 --> 06:55.714
Me too.
I feel so helpless.

06:55.716 --> 06:57.015
LAINEY: I never even got
to party in Daytona.

06:57.017 --> 07:00.085
ADULT ADAM:
<i> While Barry was desperate</i>
<i> to survive nuclear war,</i>

07:00.087 --> 07:02.120
