13:17.464 --> 13:18.863
No!
You're supposed to be

13:18.865 --> 13:20.565
my wise and reassuring
grandfather

13:20.567 --> 13:22.133
that tells me
everything's gonna be okay.

13:22.135 --> 13:25.203
I'd like to, Bar,
but look at this list.

13:25.205 --> 13:27.972
You don't have
a single useful skill,

13:27.974 --> 13:28.873
and I'm old!

13:28.875 --> 13:31.142
We'll be the first to go
when the end comes.

13:31.144 --> 13:33.845
That's not comforting.
Tell me about it.

13:33.847 --> 13:34.612
What are we gonna do?

13:34.614 --> 13:36.781
I got kicked out of
dad's pretend bunker,

13:36.783 --> 13:39.083
which I pretended first.
That's it.

13:39.085 --> 13:41.653
We'll build our own bunker
in the basement.

13:41.655 --> 13:42.787
Dad will never allow that.

13:42.789 --> 13:44.355
Then, you just gotta
convince him.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.524
To the chalkboard!
To the chalkboard!

13:46.526 --> 13:49.127
Oh, it's here.
There it is.

13:50.130 --> 13:52.030
Emory is gonna be
so awesome.

13:52.032 --> 13:52.831
Check out the brochure.

13:52.833 --> 13:53.965
They have an incredible
music program,

13:53.967 --> 13:57.268
and a brand-new
recording studio
that's open to undergrads.

13:57.270 --> 14:00.038
Or, funner idea,
you stick around here

14:00.040 --> 14:03.208
and attend the local
junior college/welding
academy.

14:03.210 --> 14:06.344
(LAUGHING) Oh!
Aww, that's sweet.
You're gonna miss me.

14:06.346 --> 14:08.346
But too bad
the check's in the mail

14:08.348 --> 14:09.647
and that ship has sailed.

14:09.649 --> 14:12.450
Here's the thing
about that ship.

14:12.452 --> 14:15.887
What is my college deposit
doing back in this house?

14:15.889 --> 14:17.689
It's a funny story, really.

14:17.691 --> 14:18.489
There is zero chance

14:18.491 --> 14:21.226
that this story will amuse
and delight me... zero!

14:21.228 --> 14:23.328
Well (CHUCKLES)
it was in the mail.

14:23.330 --> 14:27.665
but I thought (CLICKS TONGUE)
"I don't want it in the mail."

14:27.667 --> 14:30.501
So I took it
out of the mail.

14:31.071 --> 14:32.937
Why? Why?

14:32.939 --> 14:34.138
Why? Why?

14:34.140 --> 14:37.141
A certain unnamed schmoopie
showed me a video

14:37.143 --> 14:39.611
and made me realize
that going to Georgia

14:39.613 --> 14:42.747
is a bad decision for us.

14:43.450 --> 14:44.215
Me.
But wait.

14:44.217 --> 14:46.851
I wrote a Mother's Day song
that celebrates
my love for you.

14:46.853 --> 14:49.520
Just, please, listen. Um...
(PIANO PLAYS)

14:49.522 --> 14:51.256
<i> ¶ For she's</i>
<i> a jolly good mother</i>

14:51.258 --> 14:53.524
<i> ¶ For she's</i>
<i> a jolly good mother</i>

14:53.526 --> 14:56.094
<i> ¶ For she's</i>
<i> a jolly good mother</i>

14:56.096 --> 14:58.963
<i> ¶ Please let me</i>
<i> go to college far away</i>
No.

14:58.965 --> 15:00.665
<i> ¶ That no mother can... ¶</i>
Denied.

15:00.667 --> 15:02.467
(STRIKES COUNTER)
Damn it!

15:04.304 --> 15:06.004
Bust out that zinc,
'cause your man

15:06.006 --> 15:08.473
