the whole thing!

17:14.300 --> 17:15.700
He doesn't care
about the chicken!

17:15.702 --> 17:17.802
Murray, just buy the boy
a chicken.

17:17.804 --> 17:20.505
No chicken!
It's just a movie, Barry.

17:20.507 --> 17:23.441
Look me in the eye
and tell me for sure...

17:23.443 --> 17:27.345
for absolute sure...
that this will never happen.

17:27.347 --> 17:29.747
(¶¶¶)

17:31.084 --> 17:32.083
That's what I thought.

17:32.085 --> 17:33.951
ADULT ADAM:
<i> With that, my dad realized</i>

17:33.953 --> 17:35.753
<i> how truly terrified</i>
<i> Barry felt.</i>

17:35.755 --> 17:38.723
<i> Meanwhile, I figured it was</i>
<i> time to make things right.</i>

17:38.725 --> 17:41.092
Come on, Mom,
right this way.

17:41.094 --> 17:42.560
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

17:42.562 --> 17:44.695
Wait, there's no cuddle fort
down here.

17:44.697 --> 17:47.698
Yeah, I lied.
Erica, he's here!

17:47.700 --> 17:49.467
So, where's
this cute mailman?

17:49.469 --> 17:51.436
Hey!
I lied about that, too.

17:51.438 --> 17:53.137
We all need to sit down
and talk.

17:53.139 --> 17:56.240
If this is another
adorable video to con me,

17:56.242 --> 17:56.974
it's not gonna work.

17:56.976 --> 17:58.810
Actually, this one's
for both of you.

17:58.812 --> 18:00.344
(BETTE MIDLER'S
<i> WIND BENEATH MY WINGS</i> PLAYS)

18:00.346 --> 18:03.147
ADULT ADAM:<i> Turns out,</i>
<i> that third and final</i>
<i> Mother's Day gift</i>

18:03.149 --> 18:05.283
<i> would end up being</i>
<i> the most important gift</i>

18:05.285 --> 18:07.752
<i> I'd ever give</i>
<i> in my whole life.</i>

